---
import ContentLayout from "../layouts/ContentLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Privacy Policy | RCAN";
const pageDescription =
  "How the Returning Citizens Assistance Network collects, uses, and protects information from website visitors and donors.";
const lastUpdated = "July 10, 2026";
---

<ContentLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><em>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</em></p>

  <p>
    The Returning Citizens Assistance Network ("RCAN," "we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy.
    This policy explains what information we collect through rcandc.org, how we use it, who we share
    it with, and how it's protected.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>We collect information in a few ways:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Contact form.</strong> When you submit our contact form, we collect your name, email address,
      phone number, the topic and message you provide, and, if applicable, your congregation. This is
      sent to us through our form provider, Formspree.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Donations.</strong> When you donate, our donation processor, Donorbox, collects your name,
      email address, billing information, and payment details in order to process the transaction. We
      receive your name, email, and donation amount, but we do not receive or store your full card number.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Bot protection.</strong> Our contact form uses Cloudflare Turnstile to help prevent spam.
      Turnstile may process your IP address and device signals to verify you're human.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use your information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to messages and requests submitted through our contact form</li>
    <li>To process and acknowledge donations, and to send donation receipts</li>
    <li>To protect our site and forms from spam and abuse</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not sell your information, and we do not use it for advertising.</p>

  <h2>Who we share information with</h2>
  <p>
    We share information with the service providers who help us run this site, each of whom
    processes it under their own privacy policy:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <a href="https://donorbox.org/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Donorbox</a> and
      its payment processors, to process donations
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >Formspree</a
      >, to deliver contact form submissions to us
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >Vercel</a
      >, which hosts this site
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >Cloudflare</a
      >, for spam and bot protection on our contact form
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We may also disclose information if required by law, or to protect the rights, safety, or
    property of RCAN or others.
  </p>

  <h2>Data security</h2>
  <p>
    We take reasonable steps to protect the information we receive, including using encrypted
    connections (HTTPS) throughout the site and relying on reputable, security-conscious service
    providers for payment processing, form delivery, and hosting. No method of transmission or
    storage is completely secure, so we can't guarantee absolute security.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    We keep contact form submissions and donation records for as long as reasonably needed to
    respond to you, maintain accurate donor and financial records, and meet legal or accounting
    obligations.
  </p>

  <h2>Your choices</h2>
  <p>
    You can ask us to correct or delete personal information you've submitted to us, or ask what
    information we hold about you, by contacting us using the details below. We'll respond as
    quickly as we're able.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    This site is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect information from
    children.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page
    reflects the most recent revision.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy or your information can be directed to:
    <br />
    Returning Citizens Assistance Network
    <br />
    5109 Nannie Helen Burroughs Ave. NE, Washington, DC 20019
    <br />
    <a href="mailto:dcrcan2018@gmail.com">dcrcan2018@gmail.com</a> · (240) 393-7246
  </p>
</ContentLayout>
